I knew it would happen sooner or later and it happened pretty soon: I‚Äôm already not super motivated to write these notes on the second weekend. I know for sure that if I hadn‚Äôt made a big deal out of them and added the peer pressure this year, it would be quite certain that I forget about them at all again.



It was a bit of a struggle to get back into work mode ‚Äì I was pretty tired for no real reason all the time, even though I managed to keep my sleep rhythm more or less stable during my two weeks off over the holidays. And yet I quite liked being back ‚Äúin the office.‚Äù There‚Äôs something to be said about working with people you actually enjoy spending time with.



Don‚Äôt call them resolutions



Not good, but good enough: I stopped taking photos on my walks, there just wasn‚Äôt any real motivation. And I didn‚Äôt fill my Apple Watch rings on Friday, which is a bit of a bummer. But oh well, it worked again yesterday and I‚Äôll be out of the apartment today as soon as I have finished writing this thing here.



Websites



I haven‚Äôt really done much this week ‚Äì I fixed a couple of small bugs on weeknotes.cafe and I think I should write a little text of what it is about at some point soon. I did see many people starting their year with week notes so maybe I should open it up to the public soon-ish. Before I do that I want to make it a bit prettier, add a reminder feature and maybe add an option to set the language per post including an option to filter the post list? I don‚Äôt know. Marc and I also talked about the option to post via Webmention, which would be pretty neat.



Things I learned



This is something I know I knew, but somehow it tripped me up this week and now I‚Äôll remember for sure:



<?php
class A {
    public function something(): self
    {
        // do something
        return $this;
    }
}

class B extends A
{
    // do something
}

$a = (new B())-&gt;something();
echo $a::class; // A



Oh well.



The internet



Those numbnuts at Twitter removed the ability to use Tweetbot, so I guess at this point I‚Äôll even stop sneaking a peek once in a while. What a bummer.Meanwhile I really enjoy being a tester for Ivory and I like elk.zone as a desktop client.
